    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="19" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Motley</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 144.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 16, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your despatches from No. 90, of the 9th ultimo, to No. 100,
                            of the 24th of the same month, with the exception of No. 98, which has
                            not yet come to hand.</p>
                <p>Your observations upon the fall of Richmond, and the military events
                            which immediately succeeded the occupation of the insurgent capital, are
                            extremely interesting and instructive.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Lothrop Motley</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Vienna.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
